  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 55fc01baa0be7b54e8ef6801bfc93ce6, type: 3}
  m_Name: LeaveCasino
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  PromptOneButtonDisplay: 0
  PromptTwoButtonDisplay: 0
  ButtonOneText: 
  ButtonTwoText: 
  NormalDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: So you went up and left. Not even a word was uttered from your mouth.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Whatever emotions or thoughts you may have right now, I won't know.
      Not now, at least.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I'm only as valuable as you make me out to be. You'll only let me listen
      to your anguish when you stop suppressing me.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Despite your pained state, you just barely hold onto yourself.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: What are you thinking right now? Perhaps hate. Hate for me and the people
      around you.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Who knows, maybe you'll return here another day, venture to another
      casino, or neither.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Will this be the last time I see you, or will we repeat this encounter?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Will your choices be the same in the next cycle?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Will you exhaust yourself of choice where even "hope" can't save you?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I hope you know that regardless of how you change or lack thereof, the
      world doesn't change with you.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: "The same goes for casinos\u2026"
  ButtonOneDialogue: []
  ButtonTwoDialogue: []
